New Delhi &mdash; Local favourite SSP Chawrasia made history after retaining his title at the Hero Indian Open with a remarkable seven-stroke win here on Sunday.Chawrasia, 38, became the first Indian to successfully defend a European Tour title.The five-time Asian Tour winner started the day with a joint lead at the DLF Golf and Country Club and posted a four-under 68 when ending his third round in the storm-hit tournament on Sunday morning.He then carded a one-under 71 in round four to finish with a 10-under 278.AFP